  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS Implementation Audit - Core Protocol Handling Files\n\nThe audit identified five critical C source files in mozilla-firefox/firefox under security/nss/lib/ssl/ that implement core TLS protocol handling:\n\n1. **ssl3con.c** (517 KB) - SSL 3.0/TLS 1.2 Record Processing and Cipher Suite Negotiation\n   - Implements the primary TLS record layer protocol for SSL 3.0 and TLS 1.0-1.2\n   - Key functions: ssl3_SendRecord (record transmission), ssl3_ComputeMasterSecret (key derivation), ssl3_MACEncryptRecord (encryption and authentication), ssl3_SignHashes (signature generation), ssl3_NegotiateVersion (version negotiation), ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpecs (cipher suite setup)\n   - Handles handshake message processing, cipher suite configuration matching, and record encryption/MAC computation\n\n2. **tls13con.c** (259 KB) - TLS 1.3 Handshake and Record Processing\n   - Implements the complete TLS 1.3 protocol handshake as defined in RFC 8446\n   - Key functions: tls13_SetCipherSpec (cipher spec configuration), tls13_SendServerHelloSequence (server-side handshake), tls13_SendEncryptedExtensions (extension encryption), tls13_HandleClientKeyShare (client key share processing), tls13_HandleServerKeyShare (server key share processing), tls13_DeriveSecret (HKDF-based key derivation), tls13_CreateKeyShare (ephemeral key generation)\n   - Handles TLS 1.3-specific features including encrypted handshake messages, key share negotiation, and PSK support\n\n3. **dtlscon.c** (48 KB) - DTLS-Specific Protocol Handling\n   - Implements Datagram TLS (DTLS) protocol for UDP-based communication\n   - Key functions: dtls_HandleHandshake (handshake message processing), dtls_FragmentHandshake (message fragmentation for MTU limits), dtls_RetransmitTimerExpiredCb (retransmission timeout handling), dtls_QueueMessage (message queuing), dtls_TransmitMessageFlight (flight transmission)\n   - Handles DTLS-specific concerns including message fragmentation, retransmission timers, sequence number management, and cookie-based stateless server mode\n\n4. **ssl3ecc.c** (32 KB) - ECC Cipher Suite Operations\n   - Implements Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC) operations for ECDHE key exchange\n   - Key functions: ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams (named curve to EC parameters conversion), ssl3_SendECDHServerKeyExchange (server ECDH key exchange), ssl3_HandleECDHServerKeyExchange (client-side ECDH processing), ssl_CreateECDHEphemeralKeyPair (ephemeral key pair generation), ssl_ImportECDHKeyShare (key share import), ssl3_ComputeECDHKeyHash (ECDH key hash computation)\n   - Provides ECC-based cipher suite support for both TLS 1.2 and earlier versions, including ECDHE and ECDH operations\n\n5. **sslexp.h** (57 KB) - Experimental SSL APIs Header\n   - Declares experimental and advanced SSL/TLS functions not guaranteed to remain in future NSS versions\n   - Key declarations: SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro (for dynamic function invocation), SSLExtensionSupport enum (extension support levels), SSL_GetExtensionSupport function (extension capability detection), HPKE support functions\n   - Provides extension point for advanced features while maintaining API stability guarantees for stable APIs\n\nThese files collectively implement the complete TLS protocol stack in NSS, from basic record layer processing (ssl3con.c, tls13con.c) to specialized protocols (dtlscon.c) and cryptographic operations (ssl3ecc.c), with experimental extensions for forward compatibility (sslexp.h)."
}

